    <innerclass refid="classOpenSkyhawk_1_1I2cMux" prot="public">OpenSkyhawk::I2cMux</innerclass>
    <innernamespace refid="namespaceOpenSkyhawk">OpenSkyhawk</innernamespace>
    <briefdescription>
<para>TCA9548A 1-to-8 I2C multiplexer channel selector for <ref refid="namespaceOpenSkyhawk" kindref="compound">OpenSkyhawk</ref>. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>One I2cMux instance == one TCA9548A chip on one I2C bus. A DrumDisplay (or any future muxed I2C output) holds a pointer to an I2cMux plus a channel index and calls select() before every I2C transaction so the right downstream branch is live. The mux is a passive switch — the U8G2 driver still owns the device address; the mux only routes SDA/SCL.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="version"><para>0.1.0 </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="copyright"><para>GPL-2.0-only — see Firmware/LICENSE </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
